Instructions for SL@CIP

Regarding your demo video for the Code in Place (CIP) program, it plays a very important role in your selection.
Here are some points that can help you prepare a strong demo video:

• Keep your video 5–6 minutes long and do not exceed the time limit.
• Watch 5–6 demo videos of recently selected Section Leaders. This will give you a clear idea
  of what a good demo looks like.
• Make your presentation slides simple and easy to understand. Avoid making them too complex.
• Your teaching style and English communication does not matter a lot. Prepare a script and
  practice it 5–6 times before recording. (Practice makes perfect.)
• You can use the Code in Place IDE or Visual Studio  for coding in your demo.

Best of luck to everyone preparing their demo videos!
